=head1 DESCRIPTION

Contains information about malware scans associated with GuardDuty
Malware Protection for EC2.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 AccountId => Str

The ID for the account that belongs to the scan.


=head2 AdminDetectorId => Str

The unique detector ID of the administrator account that the request is
associated with. If the account is an administrator, the
C<AdminDetectorId> will be the same as the one used for C<DetectorId>.

To find the C<detectorId> in the current Region, see the Settings page
in the GuardDuty console, or run the ListDetectors
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/guardduty/latest/APIReference/API_ListDetectors.html)
API.


=head2 AttachedVolumes => ArrayRef[L<Paws::GuardDuty::VolumeDetail>]

List of volumes that were attached to the original instance to be
scanned.


=head2 DetectorId => Str

The unique ID of the detector that is associated with the request.

To find the C<detectorId> in the current Region, see the Settings page
in the GuardDuty console, or run the ListDetectors
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/guardduty/latest/APIReference/API_ListDetectors.html)
API.


=head2 FailureReason => Str

Represents the reason for C<FAILED> scan status.


=head2 FileCount => Int

Represents the number of files that were scanned.


=head2 ResourceDetails => L<Paws::GuardDuty::ResourceDetails>

Represents the resources that were scanned in the scan entry.


=head2 ScanEndTime => Str

The timestamp of when the scan was finished.


=head2 ScanId => Str

The unique scan ID associated with a scan entry.


=head2 ScanResultDetails => L<Paws::GuardDuty::ScanResultDetails>

Represents the result of the scan.


=head2 ScanStartTime => Str

The timestamp of when the scan was triggered.


=head2 ScanStatus => Str

An enum value representing possible scan statuses.


=head2 ScanType => Str

Specifies the scan type that invoked the malware scan.


=head2 TotalBytes => Int

Represents total bytes that were scanned.


=head2 TriggerDetails => L<Paws::GuardDuty::TriggerDetails>

Specifies the reason why the scan was initiated.



